revision.text:
The '''Absettarov virus''' ('''ABSV''') is a strain of [[tick]]borne [[encephalitis]] virus (Far Eastern subtype) in the genus [[Flavivirus]]. It was isolated in 1951 in [[Leningrad]] from the blood of a 3-year-old boy with [[biphasic fever]] and signs of [[meningitis]]. It can be found in Sweden, Finland, Poland, former Czechoslovakia, Hungary, Austria, Bulgaria and western parts of the former [[USSR]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Mahy|first=Brian W J|title=A dictionary of virology|date=2001|publisher=Academic Press|location=San Diego, Calif. [u.a.]|isbn=0-12-465327-8|pages=1|edition=3.}}</ref>

