{{term|term= acrostichal bristles |content= acrostichal bristles }}{{defn|1= The two rows of hairs or bristles lying one on either side of the mid-line of the thorax of a true fly.}}

{{term|term= active space |content= active space }}{{defn|1= The space within which the concentration of a pheromone or other behaviorally active substance is concentrated enough to generate the required response, remembering that like light and sound pheromones become more dilute the further they radiate out from their source.}}

{{term|term= aculeate |content= [[aculeate]] }}{{defn|1= (Hymenoptera) Any member of a group of families that include the familiar stinging ants, bees, and social and hunting wasp.}}

{{term|term= acuminate |content= acuminate }}{{defn|1= Tapering to a long point.}}

{{term|term= acylurea |content= [[acylurea]] }}{{defn|1= A class of insect growth regulators.}}

