{{term|term= antennomere |content= [[antennomere]] }}{{defn|1= A segment of an [[Antenna (biology)|antenna]]. The term antennomere is used in particular when the segments are fairly uniform, as in [[wikt:Special:Search/filiform|filiform]] antennae, but it also may be used in referring to segments of odd sizes, shapes and functions, such as the scape and pedicel. More specific terms may be used where there are distinct antennal regions; for example flagellomeres are the antennomeres comprising the flagellum.}}

