{{term|term= capitate |content= capitate}}
{{defn|1= Mainly referring to antennae, but occasionally to other anatomical features such as palps: having a clubbed shape with a relatively long, slender stem, but with an abruptly bulkier, thicker, possibly globular [[Anatomical terms of location|distal]] head, the ''capitulum''. The term ''capitate'' is not strictly distinguished from ''clavate'', but where a distinction is desired, it is that the club of a capitate antenna is abruptly distinct from the shaft, and the head tends to be short and more or less globular. The club of a clavate antenna generally is a more or less tapered thickening, sometimes hardly distinct from the shaft.}}

{{term|term= capitulum |content= capitulum}}
{{defn|1= The ''head'' of a ''capitate'' structure, such as a capitate antenna, or of a capitate [[haltere]]}}

