{{term|term= uncate |content= uncate }}{{defn|1= hook-like, as in the mouthparts of many fly larvae. (also uncinate)}}

{{term|term= uncinate |content= uncinate }}{{defn|1= hook-like, as in the mouthparts of many fly larvae. (also uncate)}}

{{term|term= unguis |content= unguis (plural ungues) }}{{defn|1= the claws at the tip of most insect [[Arthropod leg#Insects|pretarsi]].}}

{{term|term= urite |content= urite }} {{defn|1= a segment or part of the abdomen in insects.}}

{{term|term= urotergite |content= urotergite }}{{defn|1= plate on the dorsal (upper) surface of an abdominal segment in insects.}}

{{term|term= valve |content= [[valve]] }}{{defn|1= One of several appendages that combine to form the ovipositor of a typical female insect.}}

{{term|term= valvifer |content= [[valvifer]] }}{{defn|1= In female Heteroptera valvifers comprise four blades, one pair on each of abdominal segments 8 and 9.  They articulate with the paratergites and bear their corresponding valvulae.}}

{{term|term= |content= valvula }}{{defn|1= One of four blades in a female Hemipteran with a laciniate type of ovipositor, that combine to form the ovipositing mechanism.}}

{{term|term= vein |content= [[Insect wing#Venation|vein]] }}{{defn|1= Hollow structures formed from the coupling of the upper and lower walls of the wing. They provide both rigidity and flexibility to the wing. (See also [[Comstock-Needham system]].)}}

{{term|term= vertex |content= [[Vertex (anatomy)|vertex]] }}{{defn|1= (Anatomical feature) The apex of the head, usually containing ocelli.}}

{{term|term= villose|content= villose}}{{defn|1= covered with numerous thick-set, slender projections resembling short hairs.}}

{{term|term= worker|content= worker}}{{defn|1= Insects within social colonies (bees, wasps, ants, and termites) that usually do not reproduce and instead perform most of the colony's tasks.}}

{{term|term= xylomycetophagy |content= xylomycetophagy }}{{defn|1= inhabiting wood and consuming mycetes growing in wood or cultivating them for feeding.}}

{{term|term= xylophagy |content= [[xylophagy]] }}{{defn|1= feeding on wood.}}

{{term|term= zoomycetophagy |content= zoomycetophagy }}{{defn|1= feeding on fungus found on other animals.
}}

