{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox scientist |name = Indrani Bose |image = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1951|8|15|df=yes}} |birth_place = [[Kolkata]] |death_date = |death_place = |residence = |doctoral_advisor = [[Chanchal Kumar Majumdar]] |nationality = [[India]]n |field = [[Theoretical physics]] |work_institution = [[Bose Institute]] |alma_mater = [[University of Calcutta]] |honours = FNASc |doctoral_students = |known_for = First recipient of Stree Sakthi Science Samman Award |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = }}
'''Indrani Bose''' (born 15 August 1951) is an [[:Category:Indian physicists|Indian physicist]], senior Professor at Department of Physics, [[Bose Institute]], [[Kolkata]]. Her fields of specialization are in theoretical [[condensed matter]], [[quantum information theory]], [[statistical physics]], [[biological physics]] and systems.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bose|first1=Indrani|title=Affiliation,Research Interest|url=http://www.boseinst.ernet.in/indrani/indraniresearch.html|accessdate=11 October 2014}}</ref>
Professor Bose obtained her Ph.D. (Physics) in 1981 from [[University of Calcutta]]. She was the first recipient of the Stree Shakthi Science Samman award (2000)<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bose|first1=Indrani|title=SSSS Award|url=http://www.streeshakti.com/Indrani-Bose.aspx|accessdate=11 October 2014}}</ref> for her work on exact solutions of model [[Hamiltonian system|Hamiltonian]] (low dimensions) in the context of [[magnetic]] systems.
Her research interests include the problem of quantum many body systems, quantum information theory, statistical mechanics and systems biology<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://boseinst.ernet.in/indrani/|title=Dr. Indrani Bose - Bose Institute, Kolkata|website=boseinst.ernet.in|access-date=2016-08-03}}</ref>
She is a fellow of the [[Indian Academy of Sciences]], Bangalore<ref name="Fellow profile">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ias.ac.in/describe/fellow/Bose,_Prof._Indrani |title=Fellow profile |date=2016 |publisher=Indian Academy of Sciences |access-date=12 November 2016}}</ref> and of the [[National Academy of Sciences]], Allahabad.<ref name="NASI fellows">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/Year%20Book%202015.pdf |title=NASI fellows |date=2016 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150806211716/http://www.nasi.org.in/Year%20Book%202015.pdf |archivedate=2015-08-06 |df= }}</ref>
