'''RACE program''' ('''R'''esearch and Development in '''A'''dvanced '''C'''ommunications Technologies in '''E'''urope) was a program launched in 1980s by the [[Commission of European Communities]] to pave the way towards commercial use of [[Integrated Broadband Communication]] (IBC) in [[Europe]] in late 1990s.<ref>{{cite proceedings |url=https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/3-540-46416-6_52 |authors=Preneel B., Chaum D., Fumy W., Jansen C. J. A., Landrock P., Roelofsen G. |date=1991 |title=Race Integrity Primitives Evaluation (RIPE): A status report. |editor=Davies D. W. |work=Advances in Cryptology – EUROCRYPT ’91. EUROCRYPT 1991. Lecture Notes in Computer Science, vol 547 |publisher=Springer |accessdate=2017-10-19 |doi=10.1007/3-540-46416-6_52 |isbn=978-3-540-46416-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite paper|title=RACE Workplan |author=Commission of the European Communities |date=1988 |location=Brussels, Belgium}}</ref>

