{{Infobox scientist |image = |birth_name = Richard E. Cutkosky |birth_date = {{Birth date|1928|7|29}} |birth_place = |death_date = {{death date and age|1993|6|17|1928|7|29}} |death_place = |nationality = |field = |work_institutions = |alma_mater = | thesis_title = | thesis_year = | thesis_url = |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = [[Cutkosky cutting rules]] |prizes = }} '''Richard E. Cutkosky''' (29 July 1928 – 17 June 1993)<ref>"Richard E. Cutkosky", by Lincoln Wolfenstein, 1994</ref> was a physicist, best known for the [[Cutkosky cutting rules]] in [[quantum field theory]], which give a simple way to calculate the discontinuity of the [[scattering amplitude]] by [[Feynman diagram]]s.
